{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904259686,"sessionID":"ses_1d10b32d6ffeB5EC7XHcXmN86q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"functions.read:0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"Uberon has:\\n\\n[foramen secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0006678) [part of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) [atrial septum secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004155)\\n\\nNCIT has:\\n\\n[Septum Secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C34295) [Anatomic_Structure_Is_Physical_Part_Of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_R82) [Foramen Secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C34179)\\n\\nThe 'part of' relationship goes in the opposite direction.\\n\\nUberon contains mappings to the respective NCIT terms. Which is correct?\",\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86sXUwY\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"rays22\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"Good catch.\\nI am afraid neither the current Uberon nor the NCIT 'part of' relationship is correct.\\n\\n1. Uberon [UBERON:0006678 foramen secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FUBERON_0006678) has:\\n    * ~'foramen secundum part of atrial septum secundum'~ --> **FALSE!!**\\n        * CORRECTLY: [UBERON:0006678 foramen secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FUBERON_0006678) **'part of' some 'atrial septum primum'**\\n            * The corrected definition is based on the description \\\"*the foramen secundum or ostium secundum is a foramen in the septum primum*\\\" in the wikipedia article on [Foramen secundum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foramen_secundum).\\n            * The corrected definition is also supported by the medical anatomy textbook ISBN: 9632412311 that I have at hand.\\n2.  NCIT [NCIT:C34295 Septum Secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/ncit/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FNCIT_C34295) - [NCIT:C34179 Foramen Secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/ncit/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FNCIT_C34179?lang=en) relationship:\\n    * ~Septum Secundum Anatomic_Structure_Is_Physical_Part_Of Foramen Secundum~ --> also **FALSE!!**\\n    *This relationship is incorrect for multiple reasons:\\n        * It reverses the actual anatomical relationship - a septum (which is a wall or partition) cannot be part of a foramen (which is an opening or hole).\\n        * Neither structure is physically part of the other - they are distinct entities with specific developmental and spatial relationships:\\n            * the septum secundum is the second septal structure that grows down from the roof of the atrium\\n            * the foramen secundum is an opening that forms in the septum primum (not in the septum secundum)\\n        * The correct developmental ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2025-05-19T17:37:50Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3522#issuecomment-2891795480\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n18:     }\n19:   ],\n20:   \"title\": \"relationship is reversed between Uberon and NCIT for foramen secundum\",\n21:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3522\"\n22: }\n\n(End of file - total 22 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"Uberon has:\\n\\n[foramen secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0006678) [part of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000050) [atrial septum secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/UBERON_0004155)\\n\\nNCIT has:\\n\\n[Septum Secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C34295) [Anatomic_Structure_Is_Physical_Part_Of](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_R82) [Foramen Secundum](http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCIT_C34179)\\n\\nThe 'part of' relationship goes in the opposite direction.\\n\\nUberon contains mappings to the respective NCIT terms. Which is correct?\",\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd86sXUwY\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"rays22\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"Good catch.\\nI am afraid neither the current Uberon nor the NCIT 'part of' relationship is correct.\\n\\n1. Uberon [UBERON:0006678 foramen secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FUBERON_0006678) has:\\n    * ~'foramen secundum part of atrial septum secundum'~ --> **FALSE!!**\\n        * CORRECTLY: [UBERON:0006678 foramen secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/uberon/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FUBERON_0006678) **'part of' some 'atrial septum primum'**\\n            * The corrected definition is based on the description \\\"*the foramen secundum or ostium secundum is a foramen in the septum primum*\\\" in the wikipedia article on [Foramen secundum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foramen_secundum).\\n            * The corrected definition is also supported by the medical anatomy textbook ISBN: 9632412311 that I have at hand.\\n2.  NCIT [NCIT:C34295 Septum Secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/ncit/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FNCIT_C34295) - [NCIT:C34179 Foramen Secundum](https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/ncit/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FNCIT_C34179?lang=en) relationship:\\n    * ~Septum Secundum Anatomic_Structure_Is_Physical_Part_Of Foramen Secundum~ --> also **FALSE!!**\\n    *This relationship is incorrect for multiple reasons:\\n        * It reverses the actual anatomical relationship - a septum (which is a wall or partition) cannot be part of a foramen (which is an opening or hole).\\n        * Neither structure is physically part of the other - they are distinct entities with specific developmental and spatial relationships:\\n            * the septum secundum is the second septal structure that grows down from the roof of the atrium\\n            * the foramen secundum is an opening that forms in the septum primum (not in the septum secundum)\\n        * The correct developmental ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n      \"createdAt\": \"2025-05-19T17:37:50Z\",\n      \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n      \"isMinimized\": false,\n      \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n      \"reactionGroups\": [],\n      \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3522#issuecomment-2891795480\",\n      \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"title\": \"relationship is reversed between Uberon and NCIT for foramen secundum\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"__issue_context__.json","time":{"start":1778904259659,"end":1778904259684}},"id":"prt_e2ef4d911001fMve2rI9OjHL8J","sessionID":"ses_1d10b32d6ffeB5EC7XHcXmN86q","messageID":"msg_e2ef4ce2b0010ZPnS1GKROWpRl"}}
