{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778904528808,"sessionID":"ses_1d10b32d6ffeB5EC7XHcXmN86q","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"functions.write:33","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"## Summary\n\nThis PR fixes issue #3522, correcting the anatomically incorrect `part_of` relationship on `UBERON:0006678` (`foramen secundum`).\n\n### Changes made to `UBERON:0006678`\n\n| Field | Before | After | Rationale |\n|-------|--------|-------|-----------|\n| **definition** | \"A foramen in the septum secundum.\" [Wikipedia:Foramen_secundum] | \"A foramen in the septum primum.\" [Wikipedia:Foramen_secundum, ISBN:9632412311] | The foramen secundum (a.k.a. ostium secundum) is an opening *in* the septum primum, not in the septum secundum. This is supported by:\n  - The existing `external_definition` on the term itself (\"Second of the two openings to perforate the **septum primum** between the two atria of the embryonic heart.\")\n  - The [Wikipedia article on Foramen secundum](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foramen_secundum).\n  - A medical anatomy textbook (ISBN:9632412311), as noted by @rays22 in the issue discussion. |\n| **logical definition** | `intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0004155 ! atrial septum secundum` | `intersection_of: part_of UBERON:0004154 ! atrial septum primum` | Mirrors the corrected textual definition and places the term in the correct anatomical hierarchy. |\n| **metadata** | — | `property_value: term_tracker_item \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3522\" xsd:anyURI` | Links the term back to the issue for traceability. |\n\n### Checklist\n\n- [x] Read the issue and related discussion carefully.\n- [x] Checked the current term in `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n- [x] Checked the proposed parent terms (`UBERON:0004154` atrial septum primum; `UBERON:0004155` atrial septum secundum) for consistency.\n- [x] Verified that the existing `external_definition` on `UBERON:0006678` already described the foramen as perforating the septum primum.\n- [x] Checked out the term using `obo-checkout.pl`, edited the small `.obo` file, and checked it back in with `obo-checkin.pl`.\n- [x] Reserialised the edit file using `robot convert` via the ODK Docker image.\n- [x] Confirmed via `git diff` that only the intended changes (plus minor robot re-ordering) were introduced.\n- [x] Committed only `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo`.\n\nNote: The NCIT relationship direction was also flagged in the issue as incorrect. That change would need to be requested through NCIT's own curation process, as NCIT is an external ontology.\n","filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/PR_COMMENTS.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"PR_COMMENTS.md","time":{"start":1778904528796,"end":1778904528806}},"id":"prt_e2ef8cb6c001qfWt7tY031G2J6","sessionID":"ses_1d10b32d6ffeB5EC7XHcXmN86q","messageID":"msg_e2ef8c71b001zJoH3NStviFSIV"}}
